{title: Shes Leaving Home}
{artist: The Beatles}
{meta: type Chords}
{key: E}

Song: She's leaving home
Artist: The Beatles
Composer: Lennon and McCartney
Album: Sgt.Pepper's Lonely Hearts Club Band

Tabbed by DJ  31st May 2016

FINE TUNING:
The original backing track is sharp. To match it for
playing along to, use a chromatic tuner and tune all
the strings up approx. +40 cents above standard pitch.
Alternatively, to avoid any retuning, videos of live
performances are more likely to be in standard pitch.
Here's a 2003 Paul McCartney live performance in
standard pitch:
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=DIc8TnrC9tQ

TIME SIGNATURE: 3/4 (Waltz time)

CAPO: 4th fret
(Will then sound in the approx. recorded key of E)

I would recommend using the voicings in the text
column numbers below.
Regarding the CHORD BOX DIAGRAMS please follow the
information at the bottom of the tab.

Chord names & fret positions are relative to the capo
C    = x32010               F/G    = 30321x
Gm7  = 353333               G9     = 32320x
Dm   = xx0231               C7     = x32310
Dm/F = xx3231 or 10023x     Gm6/Bb = x10030
Am7  = x02010               F/A    = x03211
D9   = x54550 or xx0210     Am     = x02210

^ = Emphasise the beats

Please take a second to scroll down to the bottom of
the page and select a star rating for my tab, thanks
